    "Previous studies have shown that machine learning models are capable of mitigating attacks in different network contexts; however, little has been done in the context of drones.",
    "In addition, some of the authentication mechanisms stated earlier in this paper may not be applicable to IoT-based drone networks.",
    "Therefore, it is pivotal to close the research gap to ensure that drones meet the standards of the industry and are suitable for commercial purposes while at the same time being safe and non-intrusive in terms of privacy.",
    "Tables 1, 2 lists the related studies that have adopted deep learning techniques.",
    "Some gaps identified in the literature are that current models used to solve cybersecurity threats facing UAV networks employ a limited number of deep learning methods and have difficulty detecting intrusions due to the many types of attacks."
